The <ENAMEX TYPE="NORP">Indonesian</ENAMEX> Information Minister , <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Sofyan Djalil</ENAMEX> , declared <ENAMEX TYPE="DATE">today , Saturday</ENAMEX> , that the <ENAMEX TYPE="NORP">Indonesian</ENAMEX> government had offered cash compensation to rebels in <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">the Aceh province</ENAMEX> to help them start a new life after being involved in the rebellion .
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Djalil</ENAMEX> said that concerning former combatants , the government had allocated <ENAMEX TYPE="MONEY">25 million rupiahs</ENAMEX> -LRB- <ENAMEX TYPE="MONEY">2500 dollars</ENAMEX> -RRB- per person for former combatants , which is considered to be a huge sum by local standards , and <ENAMEX TYPE="MONEY">10 million rupiahs</ENAMEX> for non-combatants .
He added that there were around <ENAMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">3000</ENAMEX> former combatants and over <ENAMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">6000</ENAMEX> non-combatants .
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Djalil</ENAMEX> said in an exclusive statement to <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG">Xinhua</ENAMEX> , " The whole matter has been studied and all the money has been sent to <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">Aceh</ENAMEX> " .
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Djalil</ENAMEX> said that the compensation was offered after a member of the separatist <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG">Free Aceh Movement</ENAMEX> rejected the government 's offer of land " because they do n't want land and so chose cash " .
The minister said that the government had allocated over <ENAMEX TYPE="MONEY">600 billion rupiahs</ENAMEX> -LRB- <ENAMEX TYPE="MONEY">60 million dollars</ENAMEX> -RRB- from its <ENAMEX TYPE="DATE">2006</ENAMEX> state budget for this demand .
On the other hand , in <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">the Aceh province</ENAMEX> , the spokesman for the rebels , <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Baktiar Abdullah</ENAMEX> , said the money was still being distributed and that former rebels had not yet received it .
The separatist <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG">Free Aceh Movement</ENAMEX> has fought for an independent state since <ENAMEX TYPE="DATE">1976</ENAMEX> but relinquished its aim for independence after reaching a peace agreement in <ENAMEX TYPE="DATE">August 2005</ENAMEX> .
